        "name": "Elena",
        "email": "elena.gryaznova@hpe.com",
        "username": "elena"
      },
      "date": "2016-12-21 17:34:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n\n> It would be useful to add some description of what this test is doing and why it is useful to include besides other tests already running.\nAndreas, our customers run fs_test. We add it to lustre/tests to have a flexible way for issues reproduction on the automated tests system and avoid the manual efforts.\n\n> What I mean is that \"skip_env\" is too strong a check, since it will cause parallel-scale.sh to fail in our testing if the fs_test.x command is not installed\n\nskip_env () has been added to track that the correct tests env. were provided. It seems that Intel runs the tests with FAIL_ON_SKIP_ENV=false.\nCurrently we have test_mib skipped if MIB not found :\n$ grep skip_env functions.sh | grep \"not found\"\n        { skip_env \"compilebench not found\" && return; }\n        { skip_env \"metabench not found\" && return; }\n        { skip_env \"simul not found\" && return; }\n        { skip_env \"mdtest not found\" && return; }\n        { skip_env \"connectathon dir not found\" && return; }\n        { skip_env \"IOR not found\" && return; }\n        { skip_env \"MIB not found\" && return; }\n        { skip_env \"cascading_rw not found\" && return; }\n        skip_env \"write_append_truncate not found\"\n        { skip_env \"write_disjoint not found\" && return; }\n        { skip_env \"mdsrate not found\" && return; }\nAnd mallo shows that test_mib is always SKIPPED (not failed) :\nhttps://testing.hpdd.intel.com/sub_tests/query?utf8=✓&test_set%5Btest_set_script_id%5D=b10ed7ea-55b4-11e0-bb3d-52540025f9af&sub_test%5Bsub_test_script_id%5D=af769ea8-fab5-11e0-bbc0-52540025f9af&query_bugs=&warn%5Bnotice%5D=true&hosts=&test_session%5Buser_id%5D=&test_session%5Bquery_recent_period%5D=&test_session%5Bstart_date%5D=&test_session%5Bend_date%5D=&test_node%5Bos_type_id%5D=&test_node%5Bdistribution_type_id%5D=&test_node%5Barchitecture_type_id%5D=&test_node%5Bfile_system_type_id%5D=&test_node%5Blustre_branch_id%5D=&test_node_network%5Bnetwork_type_id%5D=&commit=Update+results\n\nI.e. new added test will not fail in your env.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
